8-1707.Commodity Exchange Act, defined.

Commodity Exchange Act shall mean the act of Congress known as the Commodity Exchange Act, 7 U.S.C. 1, as amended on January 1, 2025.

SourceLaws 1987, LB 575, § 7;Laws 1993, LB 283, § 5;Laws 2011, LB76, § 5;Laws 2019, LB259, § 7;Laws 2020, LB909, § 17;Laws 2021, LB363, § 16;Laws 2022, LB707, § 24;Laws 2023, LB92, § 16;Laws 2024, LB1074, § 50;Laws 2025, LB251, § 17.Effective Date: March 12, 2025
